What is the output of the following code?

```java
int score = 85;
if (score >= 90) {
    System.out.println("A");
} else if (score >= 80 && score < 90) {
    System.out.println("B");
} else if (score >= 70) {
    System.out.println("C");
} else {
    System.out.println("F");
}
```

A variable `s` of type `String` may be `null` or may hold a string of any length. Which of the following conditions correctly guards access to `s.substring(0, 1)` without ever throwing a `NullPointerException`?

```java
if (/* condition */) {
    System.out.println(s.substring(0, 1));
}
```

What is the output of the following code?

```java
int x = 0;
int y = 5;
if (x != 0 && y / x > 2) {
    System.out.println("big");
} else {
    System.out.println("small");
}
```

What is the output of the following code?

```java
boolean a = true;
boolean b = false;
boolean c = false;
System.out.println(a || b && c);
System.out.println((a || b) && c);
```

Determine the value printed by the following code:

```java
int count = 0;
boolean r1 = (count++ > 0) && (count++ > 0);
boolean r2 = (count++ > 0) || (count++ > 0);
System.out.println(count);
```

What is the output of the following code?

```java
int x = 10;
if (x > 5) {
    if (x > 15 || x % 2 == 0) {
        System.out.println("yes");
    } else {
        System.out.println("maybe");
    }
} else {
    System.out.println("no");
}
```

What is printed when the following code executes with `n = 15`?

```java
int n = 15;
boolean even = (n % 2 == 0);
boolean div3 = (n % 3 == 0);
boolean div5 = (n % 5 == 0);
if (even || div3 && div5) {
    System.out.println("X");
}
if (!even && (div3 || div5)) {
    System.out.println("Y");
}
if (!(div3 && div5)) {
    System.out.println("Z");
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 4;
int y = 7;
if (x > 2 && y < 10)
{
    System.out.println("both");
}
else if (x > 2 || y > 10)
{
    System.out.println("either");
}
else
{
    System.out.println("neither");
}
```

What is printed by the following code?

```java
int n = 0;
boolean result = (n != 0) && (100 / n > 5);
System.out.println(result);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int a = 3;
int b = 6;
String result = "";
if (a % 2 == 0 || b % 2 == 0)
{
    if (a < b && b < 10)
    {
        result = "X";
    }
    else
    {
        result = "Y";
    }
}
else
{
    result = "Z";
}
System.out.println(result);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 0;
int y = 8;
if (x != 0 && y / x > 2) {
    System.out.println("greater");
} else {
    System.out.println("not greater");
}
```

Determine the value of `result` after the following code runs:

```java
boolean a = true;
boolean b = false;
boolean c = false;
boolean result = a || b && c;
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
String s = null;
if (s != null && s.length() > 0) {
    System.out.println("non-empty");
} else {
    System.out.println("empty or null");
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int a = 5;
int b = 10;
int c = 15;

if (a < b && b < c) {
    System.out.print("X");
}
if (a > b || c > b) {
    System.out.print("Y");
}
if (!(a == b)) {
    System.out.print("Z");
}
```

Consider the following code segment.

```java
int x = 0;
int y = 8;

if (x != 0 && y / x > 2)
{
    System.out.print("high");
}
else
{
    System.out.print("low");
}
```

What is printed as a result of executing the code?

Determine the output of the following code.

```java
boolean a = true;
boolean b = false;
boolean c = false;
int total = 0;

if (a || b && c)
{
    total += 1;
}

if ((a || b) && c)
{
    total += 10;
}

if (!a || !b && !c)
{
    total += 100;
}

System.out.print(total);
```
